 a conclusion drawn from this quote:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Cleric nukes seem to have just been put there as way to thumb thier noses at wizards. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->It was not meant to be an insult, merely an observation.  It really looked to me like paranoia.  The idea that the only reason clerics got nukes was to make wizards feel useless seems absurd to me.<br>
<br>
Up in the Damage Log sticky thread, I managed to get a log from a level 57 nuking druid.  He was nuking, buffing regens etc., and using the epic snare.<br>
<br>
57 Dru ... 10,326 ... 9.53 ... <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 3.35</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (35.20%) (1084/3079)<br>
<br>
Looking at Armok's chart for an unbuffed 57 wizard using draught of ice and no click nuke, I see that a wizard would be expected to have a TDPS of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 12.160</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
This druid did 27.5% of the nuke damage a wizard would be expected to do.  This was a druid spending some mana buffing, and a decent part of combat time snaring, but otherwise he was free to nuke away.  This cleric you are talking about that was healing most of the time?  He probably didn't even come close to the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> druid's</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> damage.<br>
<br>
Cleric nukes are really not that big of a deal the way they are.  They don't need to be capped at any level, they don't need to be nerfed.  Cleric nukes are only magic based, do less damage per mana than wizard nukes, and now have significant recast times on them.<br>
<br>
btw... Grimstaff, lets look at my mage numbers compared to Armok's predictions.  Armok predicts a level 55 wizard will do <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 11.22</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> total damage per second for a 33% uptime.<br>
<br>
55 Mag ... 40,864 ... 37.70 ... 13.27 (35.2%) (1084/3079)<br>
Nukes ... 14687 ... 13.55 ... <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 4.77</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (35.2%) (1084/3079)<br>
<br>
Uptime is slightly different, but as you can see the wizard would be nuking <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>more</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> than &quot;twice as hard&quot; as the mage, to use the words you tried to put in my mouth.  I had overestimated the amount of damage I did from nukes in relation to my pets.  In this situation, it looks more like 36% nukes and 64% pet.<br>
<br>
Also.... Fynal, what levels were you talking about here?  What level were you compared to this cleric getting the crits?  Levels make a rather huge difference...  You should never compare yourself to someone 3-4 levels higher, you'll often be disappointed... that is the way it <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>should</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 552<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/02 2:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nuking....what really should have happend</span><hr size=1> Back to the topic here, but why arn't casting abilities capped for the different classes?  If our melee abilities cap at 110, then why arn't wizards able to go to 253 evocation, with mages and necros at 253 conjuration?  Clerics then would have their evocation capped at 175 or so, and they would have a harder time with casting those high level evocation spells.  Then you could further go in and make it so spells cost less and less mana to cast as your evocation skill goes up, drop the stupid cap on damage as you get new spells(why doesn't my level 1 spells scale all the way up, instead of stopping at level 4.  Every spell is capped, instead of being allowed to grow more powerful as we level, and THAT kills things.<br>
<br>
At level 50, a spell that casts in 1.1 second and does 55 damage isn't much, but for the 8 mana it costs, it would be useful against greenies.  What would be the harm since the high level of spells have a better damage to mana ratio anyway?<br>
