<br>
For the Karnors group I was basically unbuffed.  The only buffs I had were defensive(natureskin, regrowth, etc.)  I was level 55 then.<br>
<br>
Here are the things I had access to in the Chardok group that allowed for such a difference in nuking:<br>
<br>
Koadic's Endless Intellect<br>
Rod of Mystical Transvergence<br>
Burnt Wood Staff (333 damage in 13.5 seconds)<br>
Shock of Steel(Level 57 nuke which checks against conjure, my specialization)<br>
Focus items<br>
Rods + regeneration + a couple of heals came out to almost 6 mana per tick.<br>
<br>
Rods + KEI ~= 6+14 = 20 mana per tick<br>
<br>
So, the 20 mana per tick, at a ratio of 3:1, could account for 10 tdps(14.77, if we add to the previous results).  My nuking effeciency for that night, after focus items, seemed close to 100%, so as a guess, 99 casts of the burnt wood staff gave 32,967 damage in 7840 seconds for a tdps of 4.20.  This brings our total to 18.97<br>
<br>
My guess is that I missed more med ticks using the burnt wood staff so using the 4.77 to build on is not 100% accurate, thus the slightly lower actual result of 17.07<br>
<br>
Playing with the spreadsheet a little to account for 10% damage focus and 10% mana focus, it seems like a level 58 wizard with a velk robe would be expected to do ~27.85 tdps in that situation.  If he only had a solist wand(which would be the minimum required, imo, if we are to compare with the burnt wood staff) then the tdps would be closer to 22.32<br>
<br>
If I remember correctly, one of the things Armok suggested were right click nuke items to fill in the gap between the solist wand and the velk robe, and based on this mage/wizard comparison I would have to agree.  <br>
<br>
I think the cast time on the Icicle robe needs to be lowered.   While the Velious robes are much more common than the Burnt Wood Staff(or solist wand, for that matter), they are much more difficult to get.  Adjusting the cast time on the Skyshrin/Kael robes would be a good start.<br>
<br>
