For my non-item equipped wizard simulation, I assumed that wizards would meditate for 100% of the downtime, and 50% of the uptime. The other 50% of uptime was spent either nuking or standing to avoid agro. (Have I mentioned that sit agro is stupid?) While this is a very rough estimate, it works out pretty close to my measured numbers (you would expect the med in uptime to go up with more uptime, but the model does not account for this).<br>
<br>
For an item nuking wizard, I assumed that wizards would <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> never</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be medding while in combat. This matches my experience as well, where I found I was always nuking, concussion, or right clicking. The only time it would have made sense to med during combat is when melees are finishing off snared runners, but this time is inconsequential.<br>
